171 /* Note: We specifically omit the test for yy_rule_can_match_eol because it requires
172 * access to the local variable yy_act. Since yyless() is a macro, it would break
173 * existing scanners that call yyless() from OUTSIDE yylex.
174 * One obvious solution it to make yy_act a global. I tried that, and saw
175 * a 5% performance hit in a non-yylineno scanner, because yy_act is
176 * normally declared as a register variable-- so it is not worth it.
177 */
178 #define YY_LESS_LINENO(n) \
179 do { \
180 yy_size_t yyl;\
181 for ( yyl = n; yyl < yyleng; ++yyl )\
182 if ( yytext[yyl] == '\n' )\
183 --yylineno;\
184 }while(0)
185 #define YY_LINENO_REWIND_TO(dst) \
186 do {\
187 const char *p;\
188 for ( p = yy_cp-1; p >= (dst); --p)\
189 if ( *p == '\n' )\
190 --yylineno;\
191 }while(0)
192
193/* Return all but the first "n" matched characters back to the input stream. */
194#define yyless(n) \
195 do \
196 { \
197 /* Undo effects of setting up yytext. */ \
198 int yyless_macro_arg = (n); \
199 YY_LESS_LINENO(yyless_macro_arg);\
200 *yy_cp = (yy_hold_char); \
201 YY_RESTORE_YY_MORE_OFFSET \
202 (yy_c_buf_p) = yy_cp = yy_bp + yyless_macro_arg - YY_MORE_ADJ; \
203 YY_DO_BEFORE_ACTION; /* set up yytext again */ \
204 } \
205 while ( 0 )

3760 /*
3761 * If we're in the midst of parsing a declaration and a type_specifier
3762 * has already been shifted, then return DT_TOK_IDENT instead of TNAME.
3763 * This semantic is necessary to permit valid ISO C code such as:
3764 *
3765 * typedef int foo;
3766 * struct s { foo foo; };
3767 *
3768 * without causing shift/reduce conflicts in the direct_declarator part
3769 * of the grammar. The result is that we must check for conflicting
3770 * redeclarations of the same identifier as part of dt_node_decl().
3771 */
3772 if (ddp != NULL && ddp->dd_name != NULL)
3773 return (DT_TOK_IDENT);
3774
3775 /*
3776 * If the lexeme is a type name and we are not in a program clause,
3777 * then always interpret it as a type and return DT_TOK_TNAME.
3778 */
3779 if ((YYSTATE) != S0)
3780 return (DT_TOK_TNAME);
3781
3782 /*
3783 * If the lexeme matches a type name but is in a program clause, then
3784 * it could be a type or it could be an undefined variable. Peek at
3785 * the next token to decide. If we see ++, --, [, or =, we know there
3786 * might be an assignment that is trying to create a global variable,
3787 * so we optimistically return DT_TOK_IDENT. There is no harm in being
3788 * wrong: a type_name followed by ++, --, [, or = is a syntax error.
3789 */
3790 while ((c0 = input()) != 0) {
3791 if (strchr("\f\n\r\t\v ", c0) == NULL)
3792 break;
3793 }
3794
3795 switch (c0) {
3796 case '+':
3797 case '-':
3798 if ((c1 = input()) == c0)
3799 ttok = DT_TOK_IDENT;
3800 unput(c1);
3801 break;
3802
3803 case '=':
3804 if ((c1 = input()) != c0)
3805 ttok = DT_TOK_IDENT;
3806 unput(c1);
3807 break;
3808 case '[':
3809 ttok = DT_TOK_IDENT;
3810 break;
3811 }
3812
3813 if (ttok == DT_TOK_IDENT) {
3814 idp = dt_idhash_insert(yypcb->pcb_idents, s, DT_IDENT_SCALAR, 0,
3815 0, _dtrace_defattr, 0, &dt_idops_thaw, NULL, dtp->dt_gen);
3816
3817 if (idp == NULL)
3818 longjmp(yypcb->pcb_jmpbuf, EDT_NOMEM);
3819 }
3820
3821 unput(c0);
3822 return (ttok);
3823}

3825#ifdef illumos
3826static int
3827input(void)
3828{
3829 int c;
3830
3831 if (yysptr > yysbuf)
3832 c = *--yysptr;
3833 else if (yypcb->pcb_fileptr != NULL)
3834 c = fgetc(yypcb->pcb_fileptr);
3835 else if (yypcb->pcb_strptr < yypcb->pcb_string + yypcb->pcb_strlen)
3836 c = *(unsigned char *)(yypcb->pcb_strptr++);
3837 else
3838 c = EOF;
3839
3840 if (c == '\n')
3841 yylineno++;
3842
3843 if (c != EOF)
3844 return (c);
3845
3846 if ((YYSTATE) == S1)
3847 yyerror("end-of-file encountered before matching */\n");
3848
3849 if ((YYSTATE) == S3)
3850 yyerror("end-of-file encountered before end of control line\n");
3851
3852 if (yypcb->pcb_fileptr != NULL && ferror(yypcb->pcb_fileptr))
3853 longjmp(yypcb->pcb_jmpbuf, EDT_FIO);
3854
3855 return (0); /* EOF */
3856}

3858static void
3859unput(int c)
3860{
3861 if (c == '\n')
3862 yylineno--;
3863
3864 *yysptr++ = c;
3865 yytchar = c;
3866}
